238
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:27,000
Previously, I discussed that philosophy at its core deals with two fundamental questions, what is and how we know it.

239
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:32,000
Those two questions in turn lead to other questions, like how we should live our lives.

240
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:39,000
So, in this segment, I'll look at some important philosophical terms, questions, and various branches of philosophy.

241
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:45,000
For example, what are the differences between ontology and epistemology, or between reason and logic,

242
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:51,000
or between humanism and utilitarianism, or between existentialism and postmodernism.

